folder: Bedford Avenue & Dean Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Bedford Ave., east side, south from, just north of Dean Street. A view of the Unity Club Center left, known in 1908 as the Union Club; opened in October 23, 1890.

June 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

NEG # [?] 3814

folder: Bedford Avenue & Dean Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Bedford Ave., west side, north from and including Dean Street,also shown is Dean St., adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Bedford Ave. The view shows the Hotel Chatelaine. In the immediate background is shown the 23rd Regiment Armory, and in the extreme background, is seen the Fulton Street Brooklyn Manhattan Transit Elevated Lines.

April 24, 1930

P.L. Sperr

(2) The same, from a different angle. April 24, 1930.
P.L. Sperr

(3) The same, from another angle.
April 24, 1930

P.L. Sperr
